task: S2-T05
title: Test plan, quality gates, and k6 load test scripts
completed: 2026-04-05
agent: qa-automation

deliverables:
  - docs/qa/test-plan.md
  - docs/qa/quality-gates.md
  - tests/load/baseline.js
  - tests/load/stress.js
  - tests/load/spike.js
  - tests/load/soak.js

summary: |
  Created comprehensive test plan covering 6 test levels (unit, BDD, integration,
  E2E, load, security) with coverage targets, naming conventions, CI integration,
  and defect tracking policy. Defined 9 quality gates ordered by cost with pass
  criteria and failure response SLAs. Created 4 k6 load test scripts:
  - baseline.js: 1,000 RPS for 5 min, p99 redirect < 100ms, 80/15/5 traffic mix
  - stress.js: ramp to 10,000 RPS, breaking point detection
  - spike.js: instant 5,000 RPS surge, recovery verification
  - soak.js: 500 RPS for 30 min, degradation and leak detection
  All k6 scripts use configurable base URLs, handleSummary for JSON output,
  custom metrics, and proper thresholds.
